*libggz-0.0.14 (04 Feb 2007)

  04 Feb 2007; Tristan Heaven <nyhm@gentoo.org> +libggz-0.0.14.ebuild:
  Version bump

  16 Oct 2006; Tristan Heaven <nyhm@gentoo.org> libggz-0.0.13.ebuild:
  Use gnutls instead of openssl when USE=gnutls

  18 Jul 2006; Michael Hanselmann <hansmi@gentoo.org> libggz-0.0.13.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc.

  07 Jul 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> libggz-0.0.13.ebuild:
  Stable on x86 wrt bug #138482. Marked -amd64 and removed ~sparc for the same
  bug.

  02 Jul 2006; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org> libggz-0.0.9.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc; bug #138482.

*libggz-0.0.13 (24 Mar 2006)

  24 Mar 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> +libggz-0.0.13.ebuild:
  Version bumped to 0.0.13 and closing bug #94362.

  24 Mar 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> libggz-0.0.9.ebuild:
  Added ibiblio mirror and closing bug #87288.

  21 Jan 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  +files/libggz-0.0.5-function.patch, libggz-0.0.5.ebuild:
  Added patch for FUNCTION calls and closing bug #118818.

  21 Jan 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  +files/libggz-0.0.9-gcrypt.patch, libggz-0.0.9.ebuild:
  Added patch to resolve issues with libgcrypt-1.2.x and closing bug #37281.

*libggz-0.0.9 (16 Aug 2004)

  16 Aug 2004; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org> +libggz-0.0.9.ebuild:
  Version bump.

  28 Mar 2004; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org> libggz-0.0.5.ebuild,
  libggz-0.0.7.ebuild, libggz-0.0.8.ebuild:
  tidy; fix crypt/gcrypt use mismatch

*libggz-0.0.8 (16 Feb 2004)

  16 Feb 2004; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org> libggz-0.0.8.ebuild:
  version bump

  11 Jul 2003; Patrick Kursawe <phosphan@gentoo.org> libggz-0.0.7.ebuild:
  Fixed dependency on newer libgcrypt, marked as ~arch.

*libggz-0.0.7 (10 Jul 2003)

  10 Jul 2003; Mike Frysinger <vapier@gentoo.org> :
  Version bump #24164.

*libggz-0.0.5 (13 Apr 2002)

